[a href:'flexing.html']
  [div className:'heading'] Chapter 2: Flexing flexagons [/div]
  [div className:'subname'] A short tour of different ways to flex a flexagon [/div]
[/a]

* Gives a naming convention for different triangle flexagons, like *pentaflexagon* and *silver octaflexagon*
* Defines *minimal flexagon* as the simplest flexagon that supports a given flex
* Demonstrates a sampling of some of the interesting flexes on triangle flexagons: the pyramid shuffle, flip flex, tuck flex, v-flex, and silver tetra flex
* Shows that once you generalize the types of flexes you use, the concept of "sides" of a flexagon is no longer sufficient for understanding all the states you can explore

